<chapter xml:id="ch-field-notes" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Field Notes</title>
  <author>Your Name</author>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      Ingestion, not synthesis. This chapter contains curated references to external sources:
      papers, books, talks, documentation, and interesting repositories. Use this as your
      external knowledge index.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <section xml:id="sec-field-papers">
    <title>Papers</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>Academic papers, preprints, and research articles.</p>
    </introduction>
    <p>
      Create subsections for papers, organized by topic or domain.
      Include a brief summary, key insights, and how it relates to your work.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="sec-field-books">
    <title>Books</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>Books and book chapters relevant to your research.</p>
    </introduction>
    <p>
      For longer works, consider breaking into chapters or major sections.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="sec-field-talks">
    <title>Talks and Videos</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>Recorded talks, videos, and presentations.</p>
    </introduction>
    <p>
      Include links to the full video and highlight key timestamps or insights.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="sec-field-docs">
    <title>Documentation</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>Official documentation, tutorials, and guides.</p>
    </introduction>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="sec-field-repos">
    <title>External Repositories</title>
    <introduction>
      <p>Open-source projects and codebases you reference.</p>
    </introduction>
    <p>
      Include project description, key innovations, and how you use or learn from them.
    </p>
  </section>

</chapter>
